### XDT Transformation for NODE_OPTIONS

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/cloud-tooling/azure-site-extension/Content/README.md

This XDT transformation snippet is used to modify the applicationHost.xdt file. It injects the NODE_OPTIONS environment variable, setting its value to '-r newrelic' to automatically start the New Relic Node agent upon application startup. Any pre-existing NODE_OPTIONS will be overwritten.

```xml
<applicationHost.xdt>
  <system.webServer>
    <aspNetCore processPath="dotnet" arguments="."
      stdoutLogEnabled="false" stdoutLogFile=".AspNetCoreRequestLogging.log" 
      hostingModel="inprocess">
      <environmentVariables>
        <environmentVariable name="NODE_OPTIONS" value="-r newrelic" />
      </environmentVariables>
    </aspNetCore>
  </system.webServer>
</applicationHost.xdt>
```

