### Replace createWebTransaction with startWebTransaction and getTransaction

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/Migration Guide.md

The `newrelic.createWebTransaction()` method is deprecated and replaced by `newrelic.startWebTransaction()` and `newrelic.getTransaction()`. This change offers easier usage and better compatibility with promises. The callback provided to `startWebTransaction` is invoked immediately.

```javascript
/**
 * Deprecated method: newrelic.createWebTransaction()
 */
// Example of old usage (deprecated):
// newrelic.createWebTransaction('MyTransaction', function() {
//   // ... transaction logic ...
// });

/**
 * New method: newrelic.startWebTransaction() and newrelic.getTransaction()
 */
// Example of new usage:
newrelic.startWebTransaction('MyTransaction', function() {
  const transaction = newrelic.getTransaction();
  // ... transaction logic ...
  transaction.end(); // Ensure transaction is ended
});

// Example with promises:
async function handleRequest() {
  newrelic.startWebTransaction('MyAsyncTransaction', async function() {
    const transaction = newrelic.getTransaction();
    try {
      await someAsyncOperation();
      transaction.end();
    } catch (error) {
      transaction.recordExcepion(error);
      transaction.end();
      throw error;
    }
  });
}

```

